<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8903&amp;p=93953#p93953"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Examples: Hello World, moving sprite with D-PAD... in ASM6]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8903&amp;p=93953#p93953"><![CDATA[
They are optional. I prefer to use them for consistency and clarity. ASM6 also does not require a colon after labels. ASM6 allows this sort of thing:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;zero page<br />enum $00<br />    somevar         dsb 1<br />    anothervar      dsb 1<br />    athirdvar       dsb 1<br />    stillyetanother dsb 1<br />ende<br /></div><br />Any other assembler would complain unless it looked like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;zero page<br />.enum $00<br />    somevar:         .dsb 1<br />    anothervar:      .dsb 1<br />    athirdvar:       .dsb 1<br />    stillyetanother: .dsb 1<br />.ende<br /></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4871">snarfblam</a> — Thu May 17, 2012 5:58 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
